Attention!
Pay attention to the COVID-19 Policy
Passengers shall not go to the airport if any of the following applies:
  • they have been diagnosed with COVID-19 at any time during the 14 days prior to their flight;
  • they have had any relevant symptoms of the COVID-19 (fever; cough; loss of taste or smell; shortness of breath) at any time during the 8 days prior to their flight;
  • they are aware of having been in close contact (e.g., less than 2 metres for more than 15 minutes) with a person who was diagnosed with COVID-19 in the 14 days prior to their flight;
  • they are required to be in quarantine by local or national regulations for reasons related to COVID-19 for a period that includes the date of the flight.
